abstract: Afghanistan's Taliban on Tuesday accused the United States of hampering peace negotiations in response to the top American diplomat's comments that a reduction in violence was needed before a deal to end years of war could be struck.
snippet: Afghanistan's Taliban on Tuesday accused the United States of hampering peace negotiations in response to the top American diplomat's comments that a reduction in violence was needed before a deal to end years of war could be struck.
lead_paragraph: KABUL — Afghanistan's Taliban on Tuesday accused the United States of hampering peace negotiations in response to the top American diplomat's comments that a reduction in violence was needed before a deal to end years of war could be struck.
headline_main: Taliban Accuses U.S. of Delaying Peace Process After Call for Violence Reduction
headline_print_headline: Taliban Accuses U.S. of Delaying Peace Process After Call for Violence Reduction

abstract: On the final day of impeachment, Mitt Romney crossed party lines to vote with Democrats. Here’s the back story.
snippet: On the final day of impeachment, Mitt Romney crossed party lines to vote with Democrats. Here’s the back story.

abstract: KEENE, N.H. — Because of its open primary and large share of independent voters, Andrew Yang has come to see New Hampshire as “the most natural home” for his campaign.

headline_main: Andrew Yang bets big on New Hampshire (and says bettors are betting on him, too).

abstract: President Trump hailed his acquittal in the Senate impeachment trial as vindication, but the struggle now moves back to the House, the campaign trail and, ultimately, the voters.
snippet: President Trump hailed his acquittal in the Senate impeachment trial as vindication, but the struggle now moves back to the House, the campaign trail and, ultimately, the voters.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — When the history books are written about this day, they will surely record it as the culmination of a monumental three-year political battle that tested American democracy and delivered victory to an enraged and enraging president over his relentless foes. But they will not record it as the end of the struggle.

abstract: Iran will support Palestinian armed groups as much as it can, Iran's Supreme Leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei said on Wednesday, urging Palestinians to confront a U.S. plan for Israeli-Palestinian peace.

lead_paragraph: DUBAI — Iran will support Palestinian armed groups as much as it can, Iran's Supreme Leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei said on Wednesday, urging Palestinians to confront a U.S. plan for Israeli-Palestinian peace.

abstract: A guest appearance at the State of the Union and meeting at the White House put to rest talk that President Trump had lost patience with Juan Guaidó’s campaign to oust Nicolás Maduro.
snippet: A guest appearance at the State of the Union and meeting at the White House put to rest talk that President Trump had lost patience with Juan Guaidó’s campaign to oust Nicolás Maduro.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Venezuela’s opposition leader, Juan Guaidó, has long hoped to land a meeting with President Trump that would demonstrate the United States’ support for his claim to being the country’s rightful president.

abstract: The tensions surrounding the Democratic presidential race bubbled up at the South Carolina State House today after a state senator suggested that one of his colleagues had sold out to Tom Steyer, the hedge fund billionaire.
lead_paragraph: The tensions surrounding the Democratic presidential race bubbled up at the South Carolina State House today after a state senator suggested that one of his colleagues had sold out to Tom Steyer, the hedge fund billionaire.
headline_main: Tensions boil over in South Carolina over reported Steyer payments.

abstract: The slaying became a flash point in the debate over changes to the criminal justice system adopted in New York.
snippet: The slaying became a flash point in the debate over changes to the criminal justice system adopted in New York.
lead_paragraph: In October 2018, Wilmer Maldonado Rodriguez stepped in to protect two boys who were being threatened by members of the MS-13 gang on Long Island, officials said. In return, the gang members stabbed Mr. Rodriguez repeatedly and hit him in the head with a bat.
